  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\nMake DApps purchasable. Useful for freelance devs who want to sell their code on the blockchain securely and without trust. \n\n**üìù Details**\n\nThis would give the owner of the contract the ability to sell ownership of the contract. If the right price is submitted by a buyer, ownership is transferred.\n\nMerge request [here](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/3646) was rejected, and tokenizing ownership was suggested. However, this requires inheriting ERC721 libraries into a contract which may not need those dependencies for anything else. This unnecessarily balloons deployment costs. \nOther suggestions may be helpful, such as enabling ERC20 payments. ",
